what does benjamin franklin mean by this i resolve to speak ill of no man whatever not even in a matter of truth but rather by some means excuse the faults i hear charged upon others and upon proper occasions speak all the good i know of everybody what does it mean and the story behind it i think he means in short speak ill of no man but speak all the good you know of everybody as franklin arrived in philadelphia with no money and no reputation he journaled a manner of living that became a kind of personal credo or at least version one of it here at age twenty he came up with four basic rational rules for how he would live his life plan for future conduct it is necessary for me to be extremely frugal for some time till i have paid what i owe to endeavor to speak truth in every instance to give nobody expectations that are not likely to be answered but aim at sincerity in every word and action the most amiable excellence in a rational being to apply myself industriously to whatever business i take in hand and not divert my mind from my business by any foolish project of suddenly growing rich for industry and patience are the surest means of plenty i resolve to speak ill of no man whatever not even in a matter of truth but rather by some means excuse the faults i hear charged upon others and upon proper occasions speak all the good i know of everybody Contract Theory of conduct Nicomachean Ethics Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus The writing of Principia Mathematica Poker jargon Social rule Summa Theologiae Microeconomics Francis Hutcheson (philosopher) Estoppel English grammar Plame affair Merit Anselm of Canterbury Deconstruction Mojave people Philosophy of language Isaac Newton's early life and achievements Universal pragmatics Insurance Apology (Plato) Capital accumulation Philosophy of mathematics John Wesley Goodness and value theory Meaning of life Yoga Sutras of Patanjali John Wycliffe Philipp Melanchthon Victor Cousin Cultural relativism